# Pipecat Cloud

When working with Pipecat or Pipecat Cloud code:

1. **NEVER guess import paths, class names, or API signatures.** Always verify by:
   - Reading the actual installed source: `~/.pyenv/versions/*/lib/python*/site-packages/pipecat/`
   - Or fetching docs from https://docs.pipecat.ai/
   - Use `Grep` on the installed package to find the real class/function name

2. **Pipecat Cloud bot.py entry point:**
   - Must export `async def bot(args):`
   - Base image is `dailyco/pipecat-base:latest` (arm64 only)
   - `RunnerArguments` is the base class with `body: Optional[Any]`
   - `DailyRunnerArguments` adds `room_url` and `token` (only when `createDailyRoom: true`)
   - When creating your own Daily room, use `RunnerArguments` and read from `args.body`

3. **Pipecat Cloud REST API:**
   - Base URL: `https://api.pipecat.daily.co/v1`
   - Auth: `Authorization: Bearer <PRIVATE_API_KEY>` (long-lived, from Dashboard > API Keys > Private)
   - Create agent: `POST /agents` with `serviceName`, `image`, etc.
   - Update agent: `POST /agents/{agentName}` (same body minus serviceName)
   - Start session: `POST /v1/public/{agentName}/start` with PUBLIC key

4. **RTVI observer floods the signaling channel.** Always disable unused message types:
   ```python
   rtvi_observer_params=RTVIObserverParams(
       bot_llm_enabled=False,
       bot_tts_enabled=False,
       bot_output_enabled=False,
       bot_speaking_enabled=False,
       user_llm_enabled=False,
       user_speaking_enabled=False,
       user_transcription_enabled=False,
       metrics_enabled=False,
   )
   ```

5. **Two agents in one room:** PCC creates one room per session. To put two agents in the same room, create the room yourself via Daily REST API and pass `room_url`/`token` in `args.body`.
